786
00:39:28.637 --> 00:39:30.720
so Barry owes Sasha a favor. so...

787
00:39:32.762 --> 00:39:35.855
I'm trying to start a new
career later in life.

788
00:39:35.856 --> 00:39:37.358
I will take all the help I can get.

789
00:39:37.359 --> 00:39:40.113
What should I do with these... walls?

790
00:39:40.114 --> 00:39:41.480
What's her budget?

791
00:39:41.481 --> 00:39:42.636
She doesn't seem to have one.

792
00:39:42.637 --> 00:39:45.469
Huh. Um...

793
00:39:45.470 --> 00:39:49.552
Maybe a big Harold
Ancart mixed media here?

794
00:39:50.554 --> 00:39:52.683
Maybe a Joyce Pensato charcoal there.

795
00:39:52.684 --> 00:39:54.003
a Kerry James Marshall here.

796
00:39:54.004 --> 00:39:56.260
I think I can get her a
discount through the gallery.

797
00:39:56.261 --> 00:39:57.914
Andrea's brother represents her.

798
00:40:00.679 --> 00:40:02.469
What?

799
00:40:02.470 --> 00:40:05.129
I don't know. I'm just so proud of you.

800
00:40:07.637 --> 00:40:09.981
- You are?
- Yeah. I mean. look at you.

801
00:40:09.982 --> 00:40:12.287
24 years old. and you're so successful.

802
00:40:12.967 --> 00:40:15.427
- Not exactly.
- Well. yeah.

803
00:40:15.428 --> 00:40:19.052
Do you know what I was
doing when I was 24?

804
00:40:19.053 --> 00:40:21.469
- What?
- Well...

805
00:40:21.470 --> 00:40:25.552
I had followed your father to Europe.

806
00:40:25.553 --> 00:40:27.856
and I was working...

807
00:40:28.889 --> 00:40:32.219
in a bagel factory to support
us while he wrote his "memoir."

808
00:40:32.220 --> 00:40:33.637
Hey. Mom. it's 10 a.m.

809
00:40:36.512 --> 00:40:38.636
[glasses clink]

810
00:40:38.637 --> 00:40:41.094
Wow. so a bagel factory.
You never told me that.

811
00:40:41.095 --> 00:40:42.803
[chuckles] Yeah.

812
00:40:42.804 --> 00:40:46.052
I think I probably
tried to block it out.

813
00:40:46.053 --> 00:40:47.469
For how long?

814
00:40:47.470 --> 00:40:49.469
- Um... I don't know.
- [opener whirring]

815
00:40:49.470 --> 00:40:51.594
- [whirring stops]
- A long time.

816
00:40:51.595 --> 00:40:53.386
A year. I think?

817
00:40:53.387 --> 00:40:54.804
- [whirring resumes]
- I hated it.

818
00:40:56.512 --> 00:40:58.302
- [corks pops]
- Why didn't you leave?

819
00:40:58.303 --> 00:41:00.469
[sighs] I was probably...

820
00:41:00.470 --> 00:41:02.552
I don't know. afraid of...

821
00:41:02.553 --> 00:41:04.053
disappointing your father?

822
00:41:06.387 --> 00:41:08.177
I really wish I hadn't
spent so much time

823
00:41:08.178 --> 00:41:09.427
doing that when I was younger.

824
00:41:09.428 --> 00:41:11.136
I could have accomplished so much more.

825
00:41:20.115 --> 00:41:21.357
Hey. Mom?

826
00:41:22.285 --> 00:41:23.886
How are you doing financially?

827
00:41:23.887 --> 00:41:26.281
Oh. God. I'm in a fucking hole.

828
00:41:26.282 --> 00:41:28.808
I mean. I don't... that's...
I need this job to go well.

829
00:41:28.809 --> 00:41:30.636
Or I'm afraid I'm gonna
have to sell the house.

830
00:41:30.637 --> 00:41:32.678
Or pull your brother and
sister out of school.

831
00:41:32.679 --> 00:41:33.888
Or both.

832
00:41:35.553 --> 00:41:36.961
Why? How are you?

833
00:41:38.201 --> 00:41:39.472
We're fine.

834
00:41:41.929 --> 00:41:44.235
Hi. I'm so sorry I'm late.

835
00:41:44.236 --> 00:41:46.094
Traffic was insane.

836
00:41:46.095 --> 00:41:47.344
Honey.

837
00:41:47.345 --> 00:41:49.386
How could you not have
told me that you know

838
00:41:49.387 --> 00:41:51.111
the vagina man. never mind dated him?

839
00:41:51.112 --> 00:41:52.723
Oh. well...

840
00:41:52.724 --> 00:41:54.260
it really didn't end well. so I...

841
00:41:54.261 --> 00:41:57.463
Well. I'm sorry. men are dogs.
But I am absolutely thrilled

842
00:41:57.464 --> 00:42:00.229
that we are still invited to his
opening at The Broad tonight.

843
00:42:00.230 --> 00:42:02.427
You know what? I actually
lost the invitation.

844
00:42:02.428 --> 00:42:04.511
I'm really sorry. Security's so tight

845
00:42:04.512 --> 00:42:06.553
- at events like that.
- Oh. and I found it.

846
00:42:09.099 --> 00:42:11.427
Look. Andrea. I-I just don't think

847
00:42:11.428 --> 00:42:13.552
that my fiancé would appreciate me going

848
00:42:13.553 --> 00:42:15.813
to an event like this
with my ex-boyfriend.

849
00:42:16.368 --> 00:42:18.177
That is so sweet.

850
00:42:18.694 --> 00:42:20.010
But it's irrelevant.

851
00:42:20.011 --> 00:42:23.469
What I'm getting at...
is that you are going

852
00:42:23.470 --> 00:42:25.777
to this opening at The Broad tonight.

853
00:42:26.637 --> 00:42:29.530
Because I... am going.

854
00:42:39.804 --> 00:42:41.595
[footsteps approaching]

855
00:42:44.780 --> 00:42:46.154
What?

856
00:42:46.155 --> 00:42:47.781
I didn't say anything.

857
00:42:54.259 --> 00:42:55.761
How do I look?

858
00:42:55.762 --> 00:42:57.392
[sniffles]

859
00:42:57.393 --> 00:42:58.812
Like someone else.

860
00:43:00.424 --> 00:43:02.719
Good. That's the point.

861
00:43:03.311 --> 00:43:04.890
Where you going?

862
00:43:04.891 --> 00:43:07.219
There's an opening at The Broad tonight.

863
00:43:07.220 --> 00:43:09.105
Oh. wow. The Broad.

864
00:43:09.939 --> 00:43:11.636
That monument to postwar capitalism

865
00:43:11.637 --> 00:43:13.636
masquerading as accessible art.

866
00:43:13.637 --> 00:43:16.469
I'm sorry. but Basquiat is at The Broad.

867
00:43:16.470 --> 00:43:19.135
Ed Ruscha. Jasper Johns.
How can you possibly

868
00:43:19.136 --> 00:43:21.135
look down on an institution like that?

869
00:43:21.136 --> 00:43:23.355
Because it's not really a museum.

870
00:43:23.356 --> 00:43:25.193
It's a glorified. Instagrammable

871
00:43:25.194 --> 00:43:27.263
storage locker for money and ego.

872
00:43:30.675 --> 00:43:32.306
You don't have to come.

873
00:43:33.580 --> 00:43:35.330
I wasn't invited.

874
00:43:36.696 --> 00:43:38.232
[sighs]

875
00:43:39.303 --> 00:43:41.135
Whose opening are you even going to?

876
00:43:41.136 --> 00:43:43.427
Photographer named Furkat.

877
00:43:43.428 --> 00:43:46.219
That guy? Are you kidding?

878
00:43:46.220 --> 00:43:49.175
That man should be in prison.
not a museum. He's a pedophile.

879
00:43:49.176 --> 00:43:50.969
[scoffs] You know. as much as I'd love

880
00:43:50.970 --> 00:43:52.803
to stick around for another lecture

881
00:43:52.804 --> 00:43:56.435
about the moral bankruptcy of
modern Neo-Pop. I have to go.

882
00:43:56.436 --> 00:43:57.757
You don't have to do anything.

883
00:43:57.758 --> 00:43:59.803
Actually. Colin. I do.

884
00:43:59.804 --> 00:44:01.719
I have to make a living.
and sometimes that means

885
00:44:01.720 --> 00:44:03.177
interacting with people
who don't live up

886
00:44:03.178 --> 00:44:05.219
to your impossible standard
of artistic integrity.

887
00:44:05.220 --> 00:44:06.636
You like it.

888
00:44:06.637 --> 00:44:07.761
What?

889
00:44:07.762 --> 00:44:09.511
Admit it. you like it.

890
00:44:09.512 --> 00:44:10.756
You like getting dressed up

891
00:44:10.757 --> 00:44:12.692
and hanging out with the popular crowd.

892
00:44:13.885 --> 00:44:15.511
You think it makes you cool.

893
00:44:18.462 --> 00:44:20.391
You really can be such a dick.

894
00:44:26.095 --> 00:44:28.219
[lively chatter]

895
00:44:28.220 --> 00:44:29.719
[dance music playing]

896
00:44:29.720 --> 00:44:33.000
Oh. my God. Everybody's here.

897
00:44:33.001 --> 00:44:35.928
Um. if people ask if we're
sisters. just say yes. right?

898
00:44:35.929 --> 00:44:37.844
- [chuckles]
- I mean. wouldn't that be fun?

899
00:44:37.845 --> 00:44:39.302
- Sure. Andrea.
- Okay.

900
00:44:39.303 --> 00:44:40.679
Whatever you want.

901
00:44:53.413 --> 00:44:55.409
[clicks tongue]

902
00:44:55.410 --> 00:44:57.117
Here she is.

903
00:44:58.053 --> 00:44:59.887
Whitney Solloway.

904
00:45:01.220 --> 00:45:02.917
The one that got away.

905
00:45:02.918 --> 00:45:04.552
Oh. uh. my love.

906
00:45:04.553 --> 00:45:08.474
I must introduce you to
a dear friend of mine.

907
00:45:08.475 --> 00:45:10.177
Dashiell?

908
00:45:10.178 --> 00:45:12.344
Oh.

909
00:45:12.345 --> 00:45:15.587
- Dashiell Boucicault.
- Hi.

910
00:45:15.588 --> 00:45:17.442
Ah. Lindsay's mentioned you.

911
00:45:17.443 --> 00:45:19.042
Lindsay?

912
00:45:19.043 --> 00:45:22.719
Thanks. It's the name my mama gave me.

913
00:45:22.720 --> 00:45:24.886
- [chuckles]
- Andrea Rossman.

914
00:45:24.887 --> 00:45:26.928
Whitney is my gallery assistant.

915
00:45:26.929 --> 00:45:28.636
Oh. Hello.

916
00:45:28.637 --> 00:45:31.667
[Andrea] I. uh. have been
a fan of yours for years.

917
00:45:31.668 --> 00:45:33.426
I would love to pick your brain

918
00:45:33.427 --> 00:45:34.886
about the collection that you've built.

919
00:45:34.887 --> 00:45:36.745
Have you seen the Therrien?

920
00:45:36.746 --> 00:45:39.186
It will make you feel so small.

921
00:45:41.204 --> 00:45:45.511
He's a very important collector.

922
00:45:45.512 --> 00:45:48.037
- Do you know him?
- No.

923
00:45:48.845 --> 00:45:51.122
Uh. he's opening a new
gallery in New York.

924
00:45:51.804 --> 00:45:55.096
I'm hoping to be his inaugural artist.

925
00:45:55.097 --> 00:45:57.046
I'm sure you will be.

926
00:45:58.156 --> 00:46:00.094
He'll need an assistant.

927
00:46:00.095 --> 00:46:01.886
And you could use an upgrade.

928
00:46:01.887 --> 00:46:04.220
Yeah. I'm fine where I am.

929
00:46:07.512 --> 00:46:10.344
Darling. um. come with me.

930
00:46:10.345 --> 00:46:12.469
I need to talk to you.

931
00:46:12.470 --> 00:46:14.302
I think I should go rescue your friend

932
00:46:14.303 --> 00:46:15.515
- from Andrea.
- Listen. I...

933
00:46:16.591 --> 00:46:18.384
I have to show you something.

934
00:46:19.510 --> 00:46:21.469
The last time we went somewhere to talk.

935
00:46:21.470 --> 00:46:23.389
it didn't go so well.

936
00:46:25.261 --> 00:46:28.511
I think we've both come a long way

937
00:46:28.512 --> 00:46:30.969
from Paris.

938
00:46:30.970 --> 00:46:32.970
Haven't we?

939
00:46:35.595 --> 00:46:37.136
Come on.

940
00:46:39.887 --> 00:46:41.969
[soft music playing]

941
00:46:41.970 --> 00:46:43.970
♪♪♪

942
00:46:51.196 --> 00:46:53.763
So. are you gonna apologize now or what?

943
00:46:58.178 --> 00:46:59.679
[sighs]

944
00:47:04.582 --> 00:47:06.177
I'm sorry.

945
00:47:06.178 --> 00:47:08.852
I'm so sorry. Whitney.

946
00:47:08.853 --> 00:47:11.245
I was an ass.

947
00:47:13.115 --> 00:47:14.844
There's not a... a day goes by

948
00:47:14.845 --> 00:47:19.420
where I don't regret
what happened in Paris.

949
00:47:20.720 --> 00:47:23.483
That I could do that to any woman.

950
00:47:23.484 --> 00:47:25.916
but to you.

951
00:47:26.929 --> 00:47:31.849
the perfect... perfect woman.

952
00:47:34.765 --> 00:47:35.973
I'm sorry.

953
00:47:37.966 --> 00:47:39.633
Will you forgive me?

954
00:47:41.980 --> 00:47:45.090
Please. please forgive me.

955
00:47:46.066 --> 00:47:47.648
[quietly] Furkat.

956
00:47:47.649 --> 00:47:49.094
Stop. Get up.

957
00:47:49.095 --> 00:47:51.937
- You're embarrassing me.
- Not until you forgive me.

958
00:47:51.938 --> 00:47:54.177
Oh. my God. stop it. You're... Stand up.

959
00:47:54.178 --> 00:47:55.511
Not until you forgive me!

960
00:47:55.512 --> 00:47:57.720
What...?

961
00:47:59.053 --> 00:48:01.052
[dramatic music]

962
00:48:01.053 --> 00:48:03.053
♪♪♪

963
00:48:22.802 --> 00:48:24.051
What is happening?

964
00:48:24.052 --> 00:48:26.929
It's all for you.

965
00:48:28.095 --> 00:48:29.886
Furkat. please. just stand up.

966
00:48:29.887 --> 00:48:31.594
- Do you forgive me?
- Yes.

967
00:48:31.595 --> 00:48:33.552
- No. you don't.
- Please. Furkat.

968
00:48:33.553 --> 00:48:35.219
- just stand up.
- Say it.

969
00:48:35.220 --> 00:48:37.094
- Say what?
- Say you forgive me.

970
00:48:37.095 --> 00:48:39.010
I do. I forgive you. Just get up!

971
00:48:39.011 --> 00:48:41.261
I forgive you. I forgive
you. I forgive you.

972
00:48:43.887 --> 00:48:47.011
[applause. cheering]

973
00:48:54.512 --> 00:48:56.553
♪♪♪

974
00:49:02.387 --> 00:49:04.428
Stop. Stop.

975
00:49:07.387 --> 00:49:09.177
[dance music pulsing]

976
00:49:09.178 --> 00:49:11.220
♪♪♪

977
00:49:13.720 --> 00:49:17.229
[grunts. exhales]

978
00:49:17.230 --> 00:49:20.678
So. how long have you
known F... Lindsay?

979
00:49:20.679 --> 00:49:22.010
[chuckles]

980
00:49:22.011 --> 00:49:25.136
Uh. we met a few months ago at Basel.

981
00:49:26.637 --> 00:49:29.511
He's very talented.

982
00:49:29.512 --> 00:49:31.302
That's funny.

983
00:49:31.303 --> 00:49:33.427
He says the same thing about you.

984
00:49:33.428 --> 00:49:35.010
He does?

985
00:49:35.011 --> 00:49:37.094
Mm-hmm.

986
00:49:37.095 --> 00:49:39.679
He said that you have an amazing eye.

987
00:49:45.178 --> 00:49:47.719
[laughter. indistinct chatter nearby]

988
00:49:47.720 --> 00:49:49.485
They are so beautiful.

989
00:49:56.587 --> 00:49:58.462
Yeah. I was just thinking that.

990
00:50:00.187 --> 00:50:01.511
You should join them.

991
00:50:01.512 --> 00:50:03.261
[chuckles]

992
00:50:06.317 --> 00:50:07.734
Prefer to watch?

993
00:50:10.470 --> 00:50:12.428
Yeah. me. too.

994
00:50:15.178 --> 00:50:19.260
You know. I used to want
to model for Lindsay.

995
00:50:19.261 --> 00:50:20.636
when I was younger.

996
00:50:20.637 --> 00:50:22.928
[laughs]

997
00:50:22.929 --> 00:50:24.469
When you were younger.

998
00:50:24.470 --> 00:50:26.969
- Well. I meant...
- Yeah.

999
00:50:27.844 --> 00:50:29.720
I know what you meant.

1000
00:50:31.011 --> 00:50:32.636
[drink pouring]

1001
00:50:33.255 --> 00:50:34.663
And now?

1002
00:50:35.696 --> 00:50:37.928
I don't want to be looked at anymore.

1003
00:50:37.929 --> 00:50:40.178
I want to be the one
that does the looking.

1004
00:50:40.179 --> 00:50:42.803
Well. that is where all the power lies.

1005
00:50:42.804 --> 00:50:44.512
[laughs softly]

1006
00:50:47.175 --> 00:50:49.547
If you could have everything you wanted.

1007
00:50:50.804 --> 00:50:52.210
what would it look like?

1008
00:50:57.541 --> 00:50:59.096
Well...

1009
00:51:01.428 --> 00:51:03.010
Somebody would give me the money

1010
00:51:03.011 --> 00:51:06.313
to start my own gallery where I could

1011
00:51:08.716 --> 00:51:10.552
foster new artists.

1012
00:51:10.553 --> 00:51:12.386
Younger artists.

1013
00:51:12.387 --> 00:51:16.969
So much of what I see now
feels recycled. redundant...

1014
00:51:16.970 --> 00:51:19.094
built for an audience
that already exists

1015
00:51:19.095 --> 00:51:21.453
as opposed to in search of a new one.

1016
00:51:22.387 --> 00:51:26.142
I'd want to promote artists
that are digging deeper.

1017
00:51:26.143 --> 00:51:27.662
that are looking for something amorphous

1018
00:51:27.663 --> 00:51:29.676
that haunts them. that haunts me.

1019
00:51:29.677 --> 00:51:31.427
that I just don't have the language for.

1020
00:51:31.428 --> 00:51:32.776
[laughs softly]

1021
00:51:34.553 --> 00:51:36.511
Oh. my God. I sound
like a fucking idiot.

1022
00:51:36.512 --> 00:51:38.261
No. no. That's...

1023
00:51:41.496 --> 00:51:43.496
That's beautiful.

1024
00:51:47.647 --> 00:51:49.719
I've had enough. I think.

1025
00:51:49.720 --> 00:51:51.220
[chuckles softly]

1026
00:51:54.081 --> 00:51:55.240
Ah.

1027
00:51:55.845 --> 00:51:57.366
[British accent] Hello. Lindsay.

1028
00:51:58.661 --> 00:52:00.133
Excuse me. Dashiell.

1029
00:52:00.134 --> 00:52:04.257
Do you mind if I. um.
just borrow this one

1030
00:52:04.258 --> 00:52:05.425
for a moment?

1031
00:52:25.716 --> 00:52:28.008
God. you're so beautiful.

1032
00:52:29.976 --> 00:52:31.809
I've really missed you.

1033
00:52:34.929 --> 00:52:37.010
[atmospheric music]

1034
00:52:37.011 --> 00:52:39.011
♪♪♪

1035
00:52:54.808 --> 00:52:58.224
I missed this so much.

1036
00:52:59.178 --> 00:53:01.178
[door opens]

1037
00:53:03.803 --> 00:53:05.593
[whispering] Wait. stop.

1038
00:53:05.594 --> 00:53:07.553
I think someone's here.

1039
00:53:10.229 --> 00:53:12.094
Furkat. someone's here.

1040
00:53:12.095 --> 00:53:13.637
[Furkat] Don't worry about it.

1041
00:53:17.387 --> 00:53:20.386
[panting]

1042
00:53:20.387 --> 00:53:22.470
He likes to watch.

1043
00:53:31.428 --> 00:53:33.220
[Whitney] But...

1044
00:53:38.880 --> 00:53:41.380
He could give you a gallery.

1045
00:53:46.178 --> 00:53:48.220
♪♪♪

1046
00:53:56.178 --> 00:53:58.719
[panting] Wait.

1047
00:53:58.720 --> 00:54:00.428
Wait.

1048
00:54:12.136 --> 00:54:14.260
["Noise" by Zsela]

1049
00:54:14.261 --> 00:54:18.719
♪ Behind an always unforgettable laugh ♪

1050
00:54:18.720 --> 00:54:19.969
[sighing]

1051
00:54:19.970 --> 00:54:22.010
♪ There are traces of ♪

1052
00:54:22.011 --> 00:54:25.469
